==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cointension
<hw>Co`in*ten"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The condition
of being of equal in intensity; -- applied to relations; <as>as, 3:6 and
6:12 are relations of <ex>cointension</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Cointension</qex> . . . is chosen indicate the equality of
relations in respect of the contrast between their terms.</q>
<rj><qau>H. Spencer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coir</ent>⟦br⟧
